<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,500,1750]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,702,823,850]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">
Designation of a 
<typeStatus box="[403,496,824,850]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">neotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Costa" authorityYear="1883" box="[548,702,823,850]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calaritana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[548,702,823,850]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. calaritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. As is the case of all type specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1163,1284,824,850]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Orthoptera</taxonomicName>
described by O.G. Costa and A. Costa, all name-bearing types of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Costa" authorityYear="1883" box="[728,878,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calaritana">
<emphasis box="[728,878,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. calaritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are lost. By virtue of ICZN Article 75, the present authors hereby designate as 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[481,584,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">
<typeStatus box="[481,584,896,922]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">neotypus</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[595,700,896,923]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
collected at Sarrabus (next to Muravera), preserved at 
<collectionCode box="[1348,1432,896,922]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/1trn-7b59" name="Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 'Giacomo Doria'" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">MSNG</collectionCode>
, and carrying the following labels: 
<collectingRegion box="[539,646,932,958]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Sardegna</collectingRegion>
, Sarrabus 1878, [leg. G.B.] Traverso; 
<taxonomicName authority="Fieb. Det. Dubrony, 1879" authorityName="Fieb. Det. Dubrony" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoxypha">
<emphasis box="[1075,1317,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Odontura stenoxypha</emphasis>
Fieb. Det. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubrony, A." box="[151,323,968,994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="148 - 152" refId="ref10295" refString="Dubrony, A. (1879) Notes sur quelques Orthopteres de Sardaigne. Annali Museo civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 14, 148 - 152." type="journal article" year="1879">Dubrony, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. prep. ex alcol 
<date box="[497,591,968,994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" value="1984-03">III.1984</date>
, F. Capra. As indicated, this specimen was determined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubrony, A." box="[1254,1436,968,994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="148 - 152" refId="ref10295" refString="Dubrony, A. (1879) Notes sur quelques Orthopteres de Sardaigne. Annali Museo civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 14, 148 - 152." type="journal article" year="1879">Dubrony (1879)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieb. Det. Dubrony" authorityYear="1879" box="[182,342,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoxypha">
<emphasis box="[182,342,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. stenoxypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="573" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,500,1750]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1040,1066]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Remarks</emphasis>
. The first cited record of the species from 
<collectingRegion box="[815,908,1040,1066]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
is attributed to Gené 
<emphasis box="[1167,1189,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Serville, A." box="[1199,1373,1040,1066]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" refId="ref11782" refString="Serville, A. (1839) Historie naturelle des Insectes. Orthopteres - Ouvrage Accompagne de Planches. Librairie encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 776 pp., 14 tavv." type="book" year="1839">Serville (1839)</bibRefCitation>
, who reported it as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[311,545,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Barbitistes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrenaea">
<emphasis box="[311,545,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Barbitistes pyrenaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(presently 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[676,877,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrenaea">
<emphasis box="[676,877,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Isophya pyrenaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Fischer, L. H." box="[903,1069,1076,1103]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" refId="ref10378" refString="Fischer, L. H. (1853) Orthoptera Europaea. Lipsiae, 454 pp." type="book" year="1853">Fischer (1853)</bibRefCitation>
also reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1236,1372,1077,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrenaea">
<emphasis box="[1236,1372,1077,1102]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">B. pyrenaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[151,247,1112,1138]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
, stating the following: “Habitat in Pyrenaeis montibus prope “Bagnères” (Rambur); in 
<collectingRegion box="[1266,1359,1112,1138]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
Gené. Serville nonnisi mare noverat. Prof. Zeller 
<specimenCount box="[647,668,1149,1175]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
et 
<specimenCount box="[707,728,1149,1175]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
mensibus Aprili et Majo circa Syracusas reperit et mecum at examinandum communicavit”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubrony, A." box="[514,701,1184,1210]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="148 - 152" refId="ref10295" refString="Dubrony, A. (1879) Notes sur quelques Orthopteres de Sardaigne. Annali Museo civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 14, 148 - 152." type="journal article" year="1879">Dubrony (1879)</bibRefCitation>
reported it as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieb. Det. Dubrony" authorityYear="1879" box="[883,1131,1184,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoxypha">
<emphasis box="[883,1131,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Odontura stenoxypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sarrabus (Cagliari). Fifty years later, Achille 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, A." box="[437,584,1220,1246]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" refId="ref10204" refString="Costa, A. (1883) Notizie ed osservazioni sulla Geo-fauna sarda. Memoria Seconda. Risultamento di ricerche fatte in Sardegna nella primavera del 1882. Atti della reale Accademia delle Scienze fisiche e matematiche di Napoli, serie 2 a, 1 (2), 108 pp." type="book" year="1883">Costa (1883)</bibRefCitation>
described it as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Costa" authorityYear="1883" box="[767,1001,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calaritana">
<emphasis box="[767,1001,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Odontura calaritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from specimens collected in southern 
<collectingRegion box="[151,244,1256,1282]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
(Cagliari, Muravera, Silìqua and Simaxis). However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Giglio Tos, E." box="[851,1053,1256,1283]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref10482" refString="Giglio Tos, E. (1913) Escursioni zoologiche in Sardegna del Dr. Enrico Festa II. Ortotteri di Sardegna. Bollettino dei Musei di zoologia e anatomia comparata della R. Universita di Torino, 28 (666), 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1913">Giglio Tos (1913)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baccetti, B." box="[1065,1241,1256,1282]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="29 - 95" refId="ref9754" refString="Baccetti, B. (1964) Considerazioni sulla costituzione e l'origine della fauna di Sardegna. Archivio botanico e biogeografico, 9, 29 - 95." type="journal article" year="1964">Baccetti (1964)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Harz, K." box="[1253,1389,1256,1283]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" refId="ref10865" refString="Harz, K. (1969) Die Orthopteren Europas - The Orthoptera of Europe. Vol. I. Dr. W. Junk N. V., The Hague, XX + 749 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 017 - 2511 - 8" type="book" year="1969">Harz (1969)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Llorente, V. &amp; Pinedo, M. C." box="[151,443,1292,1318]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="153 - 174" refId="ref11246" refString="Llorente, V. &amp; Pinedo, M. C. (1990) Los Tettigoniidae de la Peninsula Iberica, Islas Baleares y norte de Africa. Genero Odontura Rambur, 1838 (Orthoptera). Boletin de la AeE - Asociacion espanola de Entomologia, 14, 153 - 174." type="journal article" year="1990">Llorente &amp; Pinedo (1990)</bibRefCitation>
nevertheless reported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieb. Det. Dubrony" authorityYear="1879" box="[697,857,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoxypha">
<emphasis box="[697,857,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. stenoxypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[927,1024,1292,1318]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
. Of all those involved, only 
<bibRefCitation author="Messina, A." pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="15 - 26" refId="ref11396" refString="Messina, A. (1981) Sulle specie di Odontura del gruppo stenoxypha (Fieb.) (Orthoptera, Phaneropterinae). Animalia, 8, 15 - 26." type="journal article" year="1981">Messina (1981)</bibRefCitation>
described the characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Costa" authorityYear="1883" box="[536,686,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calaritana">
<emphasis box="[536,686,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. calaritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in some detail, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Baccetti, B." box="[930,1102,1328,1354]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="403 - 479" refId="ref9782" refString="Baccetti, B. (1992) Ricerche zoologiche della nave oceanografica &quot; Minerva &quot; (C. N. R.) sulle isole circumsarde. X. Insetti Ortotteroidei (Notulae Orthopterologicae. 49). Boll. Mus. civ. Stor. nat. &quot; G. Doria &quot;, Genova, 88, 403 - 479." type="journal article" year="1992">Baccetti (1992)</bibRefCitation>
described another species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baccetti" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. festai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from Vacca and Sant’Antioco islands, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Galvagni, A." box="[743,929,1364,1390]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="133 - 196" refId="ref10444" refString="Galvagni, A. (2010) Ricerche sulla fauna degli Ortotteroidei nella Sardegna sud-occidentale (Blattaria, Mantodea, Orthoptera, Phasmatodea). Atti Accad. roveretana Agiati, 260 XB, 133 - 196." type="journal article" year="2010">Galvagni (2010)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Costa" authorityYear="1883" box="[1152,1305,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calaritana">
<emphasis box="[1152,1305,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. calaritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Galvagni, A." box="[182,371,1400,1426]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="133 - 196" refId="ref10444" refString="Galvagni, A. (2010) Ricerche sulla fauna degli Ortotteroidei nella Sardegna sud-occidentale (Blattaria, Mantodea, Orthoptera, Phasmatodea). Atti Accad. roveretana Agiati, 260 XB, 133 - 196." type="journal article" year="2010">Galvagni (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieb. Det. Dubrony" authorityYear="1879" box="[512,675,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoxypha">
<emphasis box="[512,675,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. stenoxypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Costa" authorityYear="1883" box="[733,886,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calaritana">
<emphasis box="[733,886,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. calaritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not distinguishable; however, while the two species have many morphological characters in common—for example, in both the females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Costa" authorityYear="1883" box="[1205,1356,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calaritana">
<emphasis box="[1205,1356,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. calaritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieb. Det. Dubrony" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoxypha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. stenoxypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tegmina are overlapping—it is actually possible to separate the species, solely via the varying shape of the apically incurved male cerci (
<figureCitation box="[523,682,1508,1534]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[208,1380,188,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[208,1380,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Close up of cerci of: a) O. algerica from Constantine; b) O. algerica from Algiers; c) O. martae sp. nov., from Tunisia; d) O. martae sp. nov., from Lampedusa; e) O. calaritana (= O. festai, holotypus) from Sardinia; f) O. stenoxypha from eastern Sicily." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911588/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Figures 1e, 1f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="573" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,500,1750]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1544,1570]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Costa" authorityYear="1883" box="[360,512,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calaritana">
<emphasis box="[360,512,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. calaritana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be present only in 
<collectingRegion box="[854,951,1544,1570]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
; however, it is not restricted to the centralsouthern regions, as it also occurs in the northern areas (Sassari province). There is a possibility that the female specimen recorded from Majorca (Balearics) (
<bibRefCitation author="Llorente, V. &amp; Pinedo, M. C." box="[673,952,1616,1642]" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" pagination="153 - 174" refId="ref11246" refString="Llorente, V. &amp; Pinedo, M. C. (1990) Los Tettigoniidae de la Peninsula Iberica, Islas Baleares y norte de Africa. Genero Odontura Rambur, 1838 (Orthoptera). Boletin de la AeE - Asociacion espanola de Entomologia, 14, 153 - 174." type="journal article" year="1990">Llorente &amp; Pinedo 1990</bibRefCitation>
; specimen examined by one of the authors [BM] at MNCN), with scarcely overlapping tegmina, could belong to this species rather than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieb. Det. Dubrony" authorityYear="1879" box="[1266,1428,1652,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoxypha">
<emphasis box="[1266,1428,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="573">O. stenoxypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; alternatively, it may be an undescribed species. In view of its poorly preserved state, it was not possible to determine the specimen’s identity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
